ğŸ§© 2ï¸âƒ£ Architecture & Design Best Practices
  Use ACM-managed certificates wherever possible instead of manually uploaded certs.
  Use Public Certificates for Internet-facing resources (ALB, CloudFront, API Gateway).
  Use ACM Private CA for internal/private workloads (intranets, microservices).
  Always use Regional certificates for ALB, NLB, and API Gateway (since they are region-bound).
  Use Edge certificates (us-east-1) for CloudFront distributions.
  Integrate ACM into your CI/CD pipelines for automated provisioning.
  Tag certificates by purpose (Environment, App, Owner, Domain).
  ğŸ’¡ Architecture = centralized certificate authority with automation and tagging.

ğŸ”’ 3ï¸âƒ£ Security Best Practices
  Never share private keys manually â€” ACM manages keys securely within AWS KMS-backed infrastructure.
  Enable automatic renewal and validation (DNS-based preferred).
  Restrict ACM Private CA issuance via IAM or resource policies.
  Enable CloudTrail logging to monitor certificate issuance and renewal.
  Use AWS Config Rules to detect expired or unassociated certificates.
